simply /ˈsɪmplɪ/

1. ADV You use simply to emphasize that something consists of only one thing, happens for only one reason, or is done in only one way. 只不过; 仅仅 [强调] 

例： The table is simply a chipboard circle on a base. 这张桌子只不过是基座加圆形刨花板。 

例： Most of the damage that's occurred was simply because of fallen trees. 大部分损失仅仅是因横倒在地面的树木造成的。 

2. ADV You use simply to emphasize what you are saying. 简直; 完全地 [强调] 

例： This sort of increase simply cannot be justified. 这种增长完全没有道理。 

3.  →  see also simple

